ama-pilots-republic-of-sarah-james-corden-fulwell-73-courthouse-legal-drama-frankenstein-1202546788/|title=CBS Orders Drama Pilots \u2018The Republic Of Sarah\u2019 From James Corden\u2019s Fulwell 73 & Marc Webb, \u2018Courthouse\u2019 Legal Drama & \u2018Frankenstein\u2019 From \u2018Elementary\u2019 Duo|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=Jan 31, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn May 9, 2019, it was announced that CBS had given the production, now titled ''All Rise'', a series order.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/cbs-orders-dramas-evil-fbi-most-wanted-all-rise-1202611303/|title=CBS Orders Dramas \u2018Evil\u2019, \u2018FBI: Most Wanted\u2019 & \u2018All Rise\u2019 To Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref> A day after that, it was announced that the series would premiere in the fall of 2019 and air on Mondays at 9:00 P.M.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/cbs-fall-2019-20-schedule-new-shows-upfronts-pauley-perrette-mike-colter-chuck-lorre-simone-missick-1202615155/|title=CBS Fall 2019-20 Schedule: Some Diverse Moves For The Most-Watched Network, But Lots Of Familiar Faces|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Dominic|last=Patten|date=May 15, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref> A trailer for the series was released on May 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/video/cbs-new-series-trailers-bob-hearts-abishola-carols-second-act-evil-all-rise-fbi-most-wanted-tommy-the-unicorn-broke/|title=CBS New Series Trailers: \u2018Bob Hearts Abishola\u2019, \u2018Carol\u2019s Second Act\u2019, \u2018Evil\u2019, \u2018All Rise\u2019, \u2018FBI: Most Wanted\u2019, More|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski||date=May 15, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref> The series debuted on September 23, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/cbs-fall-premiere-dates-bob-hearts-abishola-all-rise-evil-young-sheldon-ncis-blue-bloods-madam-secretary-1202632379/|title=CBS Sets Fall Premiere Dates: 'Bob \u2665 Abishola', 'All Rise', 'Evil', 'Young Sheldon', 'NCIS', 'Blue Bloods' & More|work=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|date=June 13, 2019|accessdate=June 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn October 22, 2019, the series received a full season order.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2019/10/evil-renewed-season-2-cbs-all-rise-carols-second-act-the-unicorn-bob-\u2665-abishola-back-orders-full-season-1202766547/|title='Evil' Renewed For Season 2 By CBS; 'All Rise', 'Carol's Second Act', 'The Unicorn' & 'Bob \u2665 Abishola' Get Back Orders|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|date=October 22, 2019|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> On December 5, Dee Harris-Lawrence was announced to be replacing [[Sunil Nayar]] as a co-showrunner; she will be working alongside series developer Greg Spottiswood, who will not depart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/cbs-all-rise-enlists-david-makes-man-boss-as-new-showrunner-1259767|title=CBS' 'All Rise' Enlists 'David Makes Man' Boss as New Showrunner (Exclusive)|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=December 5, 2019|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2020, it was announced that amid the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], an all-virtual episode will be produced about how the characters on the show handle the case using [[social distancing]]. The episode will be filmed in all the actors' homes using [[FaceTime]], [[WebEx]], and [[Zoom Video Communications|Zoom]], but use visual effects to replace the inside of their homes with that of their characters' homes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/all-rise-cbs-coronavirus-episode-1234572048/|title=CBS Drama \u2018All Rise\u2019 to Produce Virtual Episode Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|first=Joe|last=Otterson|work=Variety|date=April 6, 2020|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Simone Missick]] had been cast in the pilot's lead role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/jessica-camacho-cast-cbs-legal-drama-pilot-courthouse-1202561104/|title=Jessica Camacho Cast In CBS Legal Drama Pilot \u2018Courthouse\u2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski||date=Feb 20, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref> The next month, it was reported that J. Alex Brinson, [[Lindsay Mendez]], [[Marg Helgenberger]], [[Ruthie Ann Miles]], [[Jessica Camacho]] and [[Wilson Bethel]] had joined the cast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/simone-missick-star-courthouse-cbs-legal-drama-pilot-1202580879/|title=Simone Missick To Headline CBS Legal Drama Pilot \u2018Courthouse\u2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Nellie|last1=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|date=Mar 22, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/wilson-bethel-cast-cbs-legal-drama-pilot-courthouse-jessica-camacho-1202572186/|title=Wilson Bethel Cast In CBS Legal Drama Pilot \u2018Courthouse\u2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski||date=Mar 8, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/marg-helgenberger-cast-cbs-legal-drama-pilot-courthouse-1202577616/|title=Marg Helgenberger Joins CBS Legal Drama Pilot \u2018Courthouse\u2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Nellie|last1=Andreeva|first2=Denise|last2=Petski|date=Mar 18, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/reggie-lee-cbs-drama-pilot-under-the-bridge-courthouse-cast-j-alex-brinson-1202573914/|title=Reggie Lee Joins CBS Drama Pilot \u2018Under The Bridge\u2019; \u2018Courthouse\u2019 Casts J. Alex Brinson|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski||date=Mar 11, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/courthouse-lindsay-mendez-ruthie-ann-miles-cast-in-cbs-legal-drama-pilot-1202582117/|title=\u2018Courthouse\u2019: Lindsay Mendez & Ruthie Ann Miles Cast In CBS Legal Drama Pilot|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski||date=Mar 25, 2019|accessdate=May 16, 2019}}</ref> On August 20, 2019, [[Reggie Lee (actor)|Reggie Lee]] and Nadia Gray were cast in recurring roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/all-rise-reggie-lee-nadia-gray-recur-cbs-drama-1202672175/|title='All Rise': Reggie Lee & Nadia Gray To Recur On CBS Drama|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=August 20, 2019|accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> On September 10, 2019, it was reported that [[Mitch Silpa]] had been cast in a recurring capacity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/all-rise-casts-mitch-silpa-matt-murray-in-the-dark-1202730524/|title='All Rise' Casts Mitch Silpa; Matt Murray Joins 'In The Dark'|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=September 10, 2019|accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nThe [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported a 56% approval rating with an average rating of 5.98/10, based on 16 reviews. The website's critical consensus states, \"While ''All Rise'' can't quite rise above the shows it aspires to be, it shows potential for future growth while providing a decent showcase for Simone Missick.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/all_rise/s01 |title=''All Rise'': Season 1 |publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] ([[Fandango Media]]) |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], it has a weighted average score of 62 out of 100, based on 10 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/all-rise/season-1|title=All Rise: Season 1 reviews|publisher=[[CBS]] |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThroughout is first eight episodes, ''All Rise'' has been the highest-rated freshman program of the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule|2019-20 television season]]. The series has averaged 7 million viewers a week, in Nielsen's Live-plus-three day viewership.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/344226/cbs-has-five-of-new-top-broadcast-shows-abc-has-t.html|title=CBS Has Five Of New Top Broadcast Shows, ABC Has Three|last=Friedman|first=Wayne|date=December 5, 2019|website=Media Post|access-date=December 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width     = 99\n\n| title1    = [[#ep1|Pilot]]\n| date1     = September 23, 2019\n| rs1       = 0.7/3\n| viewers1  = 6.03<ref name=\"1.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = 0.3\n| dvrv1     = 2.49\n| total1    = 1.0\n| totalv1   = 8.53<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/stumptown-evil-emergence-top-7-day-ratings-gains-new-shows-1246200|title=TV Ratings: Where New Series Stand in First 7-Day Numbers|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=October 8, 2019|work=Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=October 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title2    = [[#ep2|Long Day's Journey into ICE]]\n| date2     = September 30, 2019\n| rs2       = 0.6/3\n| viewers2  = 5.66<ref name=\"1.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = 0.4\n| dvrv2     = 2.36\n| total2    = 1.0\n| totalv2   = 8.02<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-emergence-leads-broadcast-network-telecasts-in-viewer-percentage-gains/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'Emergence' Leads Broadcast Network Telecasts in Viewer Percentage Gains|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=October 15, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n| title3    = [[#ep3|Sweet Bird of Truth]]\n| date3     = October 7, 2019\n| rs3       = 0.6/3\n| viewers3  = 5.27<ref name=\"1.03\"/>\n| dvr3      = 0.3\n| dvrv3     = 2.20\n| total3    = 0.9\n| totalv3   = 7.48<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/live7-ratings-for-week-of-oct-7-this-is-us-masked-singer-1203379328/|title=Live+7 Ratings for Week of Oct. 7: 'This Is Us' Overtakes 'Masked Singer'|last=Thorne|fir