[Viperinae|viper]] [[subspecies]]<ref name=\"ITIS\">{{ITIS |id=635257 |taxon=''Vipera berus bosniensis'' |accessdate=16 August 2006}}</ref> [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Balkans|Balkan Peninsula]].<ref name=\"Mal03\">Mallow D, Ludwig D, Nilson G. 2003. ''True Vipers: Natural History and Toxinology of Old World Vipers''. Malabar, Florida: Krieger Publishing Company. 359 pp. {{ISBN|0-89464-877-2}}.</ref>\n\n==Geographic range==\nIt is only found within the Balkan Peninsula, particularly the [[Herzegovina]] region of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], hence its common name.<ref name=\"Mal03\"/>\n\n==Taxonomy==\nMcDiarmid et al. (1999) follow Golay et al. (1993) and recognize ''V. b. bosniensis'' as a subspecies of ''V. berus''.<ref name=\"McD99\"/> However, it has been considered a full [[species]] in recent literature.<ref name=\"Mal03\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n* Golay P, [[Hobart Muir Smith|Smith HM]], [[:fr:Donald George Broadley|Broadley DG]], [[James R. Dixon|Dixon JR]], McCarthy CJ, Rage J-C, Sch\u00e4tti B, Toriba M. 1993. ''Endoglyphs and Other Major Venomous Snakes of the World. A Checklist.'' Geneva: Azemiops. 478 pp.\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NRDB species|genus=Vipera|species=berus|date=21 November|year=2007}}\n* '''Photograph''' of ''Vipera berus bosniensis'' [http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/photo/HHdLwlIQVzuYKH_2GL_uBA]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3511654}}\n\n[[Category:Vipera|berus|bosniensis]]\n[[Category:Reptiles described in 1889]]\n", "text_old": "{{Subspeciesbox\n| image =\n| genus = Vipera\n| species = berus\n| subspecies = bosniensis\n| authority = [[Oskar Boettger|Boettger]], 1889\n| synonyms = * ''Vipera berus'' var. ''bosniensis'' <small>Boettger ''In'' [[Johann August Georg Edmund Mojsisovics von Mojsvar|Mojsisovics]], 1889</small>\n* ''Vipera berus'' var. ''pseudaspis'' <small>[[Egid Schreiber|Schreiber]], 1912</small>\n* ''Vipera coronis coronis'' <br><small>[[:fr:Albert Franz Theodor Reuss|A.F. Re