{"title_page": "Trials (series)", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox VG series\n| title              = Trials\n| image              = File:Trials-Logo-Black.png\n| caption            = \n| developer          = [[RedLynx]]\n| publisher          = [[Ubisoft]]\n| platforms          =  [[Java (software platform)|Java]], [[Adobe Flash|Flash]], [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], [[Xbox 360]], [[Xbox One]], [[PlayStation 4]], [[Nintendo Switch]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Stadia]]\n| first release version  = ''Trials''\n| first release date     = 2000\n| latest release version = ''[[Trials Rising]]''\n| latest release date    = 26 February 2019\n| genre              = [[Racing game|Racing]], [[Platform game|Platformer]]\n| spinoffs           = \n}}\n'''''Trials''''' is a platform racing video game series developed by [[RedLynx]], loosely based on the real-life sport of [[motorcycle trials]]. It involves a motorcycle rider in a [[2.5D]] world, traversing obstacles under the influence of simulated physics. It was published by [[Ubisoft]].\n\n==History==\n''Trials'' was released as a [[browser game]] in 2000. The gameplay was somewhat similar to [[Mastertronic]]'s 1987 hit ''[[Kikstart 2]]''.\n\n''Trials 2'' was released in 2007, and remade as ''[[Trials 2: Second Edition]]'' in 2008. ''[[Trials HD]]'' was released for the [[Xbox Live Arcade]] in 2009. ''[[Trials Evolution]]'' was released for the Xbox Live Arcade in 2012. ''Trials Frontier'' was released for smart phones and tablets on 10 April 2014.\n\n''[[Trials Fusion]]'' released for PlayStation 4, Xbox 360, and Xbox One on 16 April 2014. ''Trials Frontier'' and ''Trials Fusion'' are designed to work together.<ref name=\"Polygon Fusion/Frontier announcement\"/> ''Trials Fusion'' was released for the PC on 24 April 2014.<ref name=\"OXM Fusion first screens\"/>\n\nOn 11 June 2018 ''[[Trials Rising]]'' was announced by RedLynx at E3 2018. It was released for PlayStation 4, Xbox One, Nintendo Switch, and PC on 26 February 2019 and for Stadia on 19 November 2019.\n\n==Games==\n===Main series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n!Platform\n|-\n| ''Trials'' || 2000 || [[Java (software platform)|Java]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.redlynxtrials.com/trialslegends/history/|title=History of Trials|work=RedLynx Trials|publisher=[[RedLynx]]|accessdate=27 February 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Trials 2'' || 2007 ||  [[Adobe Flash|Flash]]\n|-\n| ''[[Trials HD]]'' || 2009 || [[Xbox 360]]\n|-\n| ''[[Trials Evolution]]'' || 2012 || Xbox 360\n|-\n| ''[[Trials Fusion]]'' || 2014 || Microsoft Windows, [[PlayStation 4]], Xbox 360, [[Xbox One]]\n|-\n| ''[[Trials Rising]]'' || 2019 || Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, Xbox One, [[Nintendo Switch]], [[Google Stadia|Stadia]]\n|}\n\n===Other games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Title\n!Year\n!Platform\n!Type\n|-\n| ''Trials Bike Basic'' || 2003 || Java || Expansion\n|-\n| ''Trials Bike Pro'' || 2003 || Java || Expansion\n|-\n| ''Trials Construction Yard'' || 2004 || Java || Expansion\n|-\n| ''Trials Mountain Heights'' || 2005 || Java || Expansion\n|-\n| ''Trials Dynamite Tumble'' || 2008 || Flash || Spin-off\n|-\n| ''[[Trials 2: Second Edition]]'' || 2008 || Microsoft Windows || Remake\n|-\n| ''Trials Legends'' || 2010 || Microsoft Windows || Remake\n|-\n| ''Trials Evolution: Gold Edition'' || 2013 || Microsoft Windows || Remake\n|-\n| ''[[Trials Frontier]]'' || 2014 || [[Android (operating system)|Android]], iOS || Spin-off\n|-\n| ''[[Trials of the Blood Dragon]]'' || 2016 || Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, Xbox One || Spin-off\n|}\n\n== References ==\n\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"OXM Fusion first screens\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oxm.co.uk/68314/first-in-game-trials-fusion-screenshots-arrive/?site=us |accessdate=December 20, 2013 |title=First in-game Trials Fusion screenshots arrive |last1=Evans-Thirlwell |first1=Edwin |date=December 19, 2013 |work=[[Official Xbox Magazine]] |publisher=[