{"title_page": "1991\u201392 Sheffield Wednesday F.C. season", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox football club season\n|club=[[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]]\n|season=1991\u201392\n|manager=[[Trevor Francis]] ''(player-manager)''\n|chairman=[[Dave Richards]]\n|stadium=[[Hillsborough Stadium|Hillsborough]]\n|league=[[Football League First Division|First Division]]\n|league result=[[1991\u201392 Football League#First Division|3rd]]\n|cup1=[[FA Cup]]\n|cup1 result=[[1991\u201392 FA Cup#Fourth round proper|Fourth round]]\n|cup2=[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n|cup2 result=[[1991\u201392 Football League Cup|Third round]]\n|cup3=[[Full Members Cup]]\n|cup3 result=[[1991\u201392 Full Members Cup|Quarter finals]]\n|league topscorer=[[David Hirst (footballer)|Hirst]] (18)\n|season topscorer=Hirst (21)\n|highest attendance=\n|lowest attendance=\n|average attendance=29,578\n|prevseason=[[1990\u201391 Sheffield Wednesday F.C. season|1990\u201391]]\n|nextseason=[[1992\u201393 Sheffield Wednesday F.C. season|1992\u201393]]\n}}\nDuring the 1991\u201392 English football season, [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.]] competed in the [[Football League First Division]], following promotion from the [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] the previous season.\n\n==Season summary==\nHaving guided Sheffield Wednesday to promotion to the First Division and League Cup glory the previous season, [[Ron Atkinson]] left Wednesday for [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] (in somewhat controversial circumstances, having claimed that he was staying on at Wednesday before departing a week later). He was replaced by striker [[Trevor Francis]], who juggled his playing responsibilities with his management role. Under Francis, Wednesday enjoyed a fabulous season, finishing third, behind [[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]] and [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and ahead of bigger clubs like [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]; this gave Wednesday qualification to the [[UEFA Cup]].\n\nDespite their overall good form, Wednesday still found themselves on the receiving ends of the season's heaviest home (6-1 to Leeds) and away (7-1 to Arsenal) defeats. Wednesday also lost both of that season's [[Steel City derby|derbies]] against arch-rivals [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]], losing 1-3 at home and 2-0 at [[Bramall Lane]].\n\n==Final league table==\n{{main|1991\u201392 Football League First Division}}\n{{:1991\u201392 Football League First Division|only_totals=y|showteam=SHW}}\n\n==Results==\n''Sheffield Wednesday's score comes first''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.statto.com/football/teams/sheffield-wednesday/1991-1992/results |title=Archived copy |access-date=25 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906042057/http://www.statto.com/football/teams/sheffield-wednesday/1991-1992/results |archive-date=6 September 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Legend===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|style=\"background-color: #d0ffe3;\"|<small>Win</small>\n|style=\"background-color: #ffffdd;\"|<small>Draw</small>\n|style=\"background-color: #ffd0e3;\"|<small>Loss</small>\n|}\n\n===Football League First Division===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background-color: #ffd0e3;\"\n| 17 August 1991 ||[[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]||H||2\u20133||36,749||[[David Hirst (footballer)|Hirst]], [[Danny Wilson (footballer, born 1960)|Wilson]]\n|-style=\"background-color: #ffffdd;\"\n| 24 August 1991 ||[[Leeds United A.F.C.|Leeds United]]||A||1\u20131||30,260||[[David Hirst (footballer)|Hirst]]\n|-style=\"background-color: #d0ffe3;\"\n| 28 August 1991 ||[[Everton F.C.|Everton]]||H||2\u20131||28,690||[[Viv Anderson|Anderson]], [[Danny Wilson (footballer, born 1960)|Wilson]]\n|-style=\"background-color: #d0ffe3;\"\n| 31 August 1991 ||[[